<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="b30Dec1938"><font color="red">30 December 1938</font> <i>NLHW</i> (from Harriet Weaver to Paul L&eacute;on): I like the format of the paged proofs &hellip; P.S. In looking through the first few pages of Part I I have noticed four errors: p.4, line 6. Surely there should either be a comma after larms (not a full stop) or else a capital A for appalling. p.5, par 3, line 15. for some day read some say, &mdash; according to the original text p.9 line 4 for linew read lines &mdash; p.10 line 15 for boy Hney read boy. Hney </div>
